cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a theoretical framework for the cooperative planning of renewable generations in a system of interconnected microgrids, which involves control and optimization of the energy generation and distribution systems. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper designs a fair cost sharing method based on Nash bargaining to incentivize cooperative planning, which involves game-theoretic analysis and optimization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper may involve machine learning techniques for data analysis and prediction of renewable energy generation. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves computational modeling and optimization of the renewable energy generation and distribution systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software development for implementing the proposed cooperative planning framework.
